CatDescriptText: Mrs. Neyda Moses, worker for Manhattan Music, 616 Amity Street, Homestead, was part of a man on the street column entitled "Amos 'n' Andy Television Show Offends Some, Pleases Others," published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 28, 1951, pg. 3
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Neyda Moses wearing light colored short sleeved patterned blouse, ring, and wristwatch, posed behind counter in front of shelves of files and pamphlets
